Tree-ring width decreases with age in mature trees due to the diameter growth of the stem. Therefore, BAI is more appropriate than DBHI (diameter at breast height increment) for modeling tree growth and forest productivity. BAI was estimated according to the following formula:1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
